tutional Law, first published in 1978 and still taught in virtually every l=
aw school in America. Not incidentally, Tribe is also a 36-time litigator b=
efore the Supreme Court, and has
served as a legal tutor to a staggering number of political and judicial em=
inences across the ideological spectrum, from Barack Obama and Elena Kagan =
to John Roberts and Ted Cruz. In our conversation, Tribe contended that the=
