=C2=A0

Laurence Tribe: I think it is obviously a coup, an inside coup, and not onl=
y by people in power who are now consolidating their power, but by people w=
ho were never elected to power. It has to be called a coup because it meets=
 all the criteria; it is an
attempt to use the instruments of power to displace the entire structure of=
 government that we have nurtured and inherited over two centuries. And it=
=E2=80=99s happening at blinding speed, so it=E2=80=99s very hard to see ex=
actly where it=E2=80=99s going.

=C2=A0

One of the surprising things is that it=E2=80=99s happening so quickly and =
with so little systematic planning that it is quite possible that it will c=
